* Add go-server.service to /etc/init.d/go-server. Make sure to replace the
variable values in the file with the actual desired values.
* Run sudo update-rc.d go-server defaults to install the service. Now service
go-server {start,stop,restart} should be usable.
* You can just startup the server manually at this point (sudo service go-server
start), or you can reboot once to verify that it start on boot.


Locally:

$ go build server.go
$ scp -i ~/my-key-pair.pem ./server ubuntu@server-ip-address:~
$ ssh -i ~/my-key-pair.pem ubuntu@server-ip-address

At Ubuntu instance:

$ sudo service go-server stop
$ sudo mv server /usr/local/bin/goserver
$ sudo service go-server start
